.TH "touch_softlockup_watchdog_sched" 9 "touch_softlockup_watchdog_sched" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
touch_softlockup_watchdog_sched \- touch watchdog on scheduler stalls
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "notrace void" touch_softlockup_watchdog_sched
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Call when the scheduler may have stalled for legitimate reasons
preventing the watchdog task from executing - e.g. the scheduler
entering idle state.  This should only be used for scheduler events.
Use \fBtouch_softlockup_watchdog\fP for everything else.
